SPORT: Rugby World Cup - England v Fiji
On: itv HD   
Date: Friday 18th September 2015 
Time: 19:25 to 22:15 

Hosts England get the 2015 World Cup under way in the first live match of the tournament against Fiji at Twickenham. With Wales and Australia to come in Group A, it is a must-win match for Stuart Lancaster's men, but the Fijians are no pushovers, having won the Pacific Cup last month. John Inverdale is joined in the studio by three men who inspired England to World Cup glory in 2003 - Jonny Wilkinson, Lawrence Dallaglio and Sir Clive Woodward. Commentary comes from Nick Mullins and Ben Kay.

This is the complete ITV coverage in English and includes pre-match build-up, half-time analysis and post match interviews.
